The nature of the brand and related terms. Relationships between brand management and marketing and design. Values and brand architecture. Brand levels: organization, product group, product/service.The specifics and necessity of creating personal brands. Telling stories as part of brand. management.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide the knowledge about the connections between brand management, and marketing and design management, and to develop the ability to analyse and create brands.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understands the nature of the brand and its connection with design and marketing; 2) knows the specifics of brand creation and brand management and the process at the level of organization, product/service, person; 3) can analyse brand strategy and create a brand management plan; 4) is able to compose an advertising text in accordance with the brand architecture; 5) analyzes the brand's visual identity and makes proposals based on it.
